stylometry: A logical upper limit is the best possible solution.It is the maxium that a particular value could be and a limiting constraint in a model. It is used in a fixed cost models where by producing any amount of a  product incurs a fix cost by doing so. For example, lets say a company is creating T shirts. The logical upper limit takes the amount of materals it costs to create the t shirts and divides it by how many raw materials the company possesses. In a fixed cost model, the logical upper limit can be used to show how many t shirts could be made with an endless amount of materials while satisfying the fixed cost constraint. We can set this up by setting the logical upper limit to binary 0-1 which basically tells solver to choose to create a t shirt or not. By doing this solver than can choose which t shirt would create the best profit while satisfying the fixed cost constraint.
